        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 44,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-30T14:30:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I just looked at the comments for SkEncodedInfo::Color, and it says:\n\n    /*\n     * We strive to make the number of components per pixel obvious through\n     * our naming conventions.\n     * Ex: kRGB has 3 components.  kRGBA has 4 components.\n     *\n     * This sometimes results in redundant Alpha and Color information.\n     * Ex: kRGB images must also be kOpaque.\n     */\n\nTo be consistent with the current convention, this should be kRGBX_Color. (That doesn\u0027t currently exist, because we haven\u0027t seen it in existing formats, but there is already a kBGRX.)\n\nIn practice, this would only matter internally if you had an SkSwizzler, which would think you only had three components instead of four.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 44,
        "startChar": 35,
        "endLine": 44,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "7e27e34c075a9ce09c8cb97c81f1341df5854ea8",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8988e8f5_67d86242",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkDumbCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 215,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-30T14:30:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why not skip recording minRowBytes, given that it\u0027s redundant?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 215,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 215,
        "endChar": 37
      },
      "revId": "7e27e34c075a9ce09c8cb97c81f1341df5854ea8",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
